Just like how our billet lower receiver utilizes set screws to retain everything in place, the forward assist is held in place with a set screw for easy disassembly if you ever need to in the life of this upper receiver. Our billet upper receiver matches our billet lower perfectly, but it also works great with standard forged lowers so it’s fully up to you on which receiver you want to use. title: For Sale:  1918 Colt New Service Rare Type
postcontent: A very rare Colt New Service in .38-40 WCF with a lanyard loop attachment. This gun dates to 1918 and Was built on a spare model 1917 frame, since Colt's government contract had just ended, there were still many parts lying around. All model 1917s were in .45 ACP using moon clips, so this was a gun produced for the civilian market. Given that the war ended in November, there is but a 1 and a half month window in which this revolver could have been built. This variant is therefore very uncommon. The condition is very good, the cylinder is tight with only a tiny bit of slop. I have fired it quite a bit and it performs very well. The bore is clean and the rifling is strong. The nickel is not factory but it was done very well and is quite old. The only flaking is on the hammer where it interfaces with the frame. price is negotiable.
